section.section:
The Committee consists of the following members:
the Secretary of General Services, or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of Budget and Management, or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of Natural Resources, or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of the Environment, or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene, or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of Business and Economic Development, or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of Transportation, or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of Public Safety and Correctional Services, or the Secretary's designee; and
the Chancellor of the University System of Maryland, or the Chancellor's designee.

text.section:
The Committee shall provide the State with information and assistance regarding environmentally preferable purchasing, including:
the promotion of environmentally preferable purchasing;
the development and implementation of a strategy to increase environmentally preferable purchasing that may include the development of statewide policies, guidelines, programs, and regulations;
coordination with other State or federal agencies, task forces, workgroups, regulatory efforts, research and data collection efforts, or other programs and services relating to environmentally preferable purchasing; and
the development of an environmentally preferable purchasing best practices manual that may be adopted from other governmental or nongovernmental institutions.
